column13: FIELD: chemistry. ^ SUBSTANCE: rape-seed oil is treated with ethyl alcohol through re-esterification in volume ratio 0.5-1.0:10-15 until achieving homogeneous state. The obtained mixture is fed into a reactor in which re-esterification takes place at temperature 250-280C, pressure 15-20 MPa, for 5-10 minutes. The mixture is cooled and then fed into an extractor. The mixture is the extracted with carbon dioxide in supercritical conditions with carbon dioxide flow rate of 20-35 l/h, temperature 240-260C and pressure 15-20 MPa. The obtained homogeneous mixture is fed into a first separator for separation of glycerine from the end product at pressure 0.5 MPa and temperature 20-30C. The end product is fed into a second separator for separation of fatty acid ethyl alcohol from carbon dioxide at pressure 0.2-0.3 MPa and temperature 5-10C. The end product is fed into the second separator for separation of carbon dioxide at pressure 0.1-0.15 MPa and temperature 10-20C. Carbon dioxide separated in the second separator is preferably recycled. ^ EFFECT: simple process. ^ 2 cl, 1 tbl, 2 ex

column13: FIELD: chemistry. ^ SUBSTANCE: invention relates to method of obtaining ethers of fatty acids, which can be applied as biodiesel - alternative biofuel. Described is method of rapeseed oil processing by its re-etherification with ethyl alcohol, with separation of obtained products into fractions, obtained barbotage with carbon dioxin of immobilised granulated yeasts biomass, is realised in reactor at 350-400C and pressure 35-50 MPa with following cooling of mixture, oven control in extractor to 250C, extraction with carbon dioxide in overcritical conditions at 350C and pressure 35 MPa. Obtained homogenous mixture is supplied into first separator for separation of glycerin from target product, and then target product is supplied to second separator for separation of fatty acid ethyl ether from carbon dioxin, which is directed to recycling. ^ EFFECT: simplification of technological process and improvement of ecology due to application of overcritical ethyl alcohol, and obtaining of target product with conversion 95% and higher. ^ 2 cl, 2 ex

column13: FIELD: chemistry. ^ SUBSTANCE: invention relates to methods of producing organomineral fertiliser from wastes of processing enterprises and can be used in agriculture to increase soil fertility and improve soil structure. The method involves obtaining organomineral fertiliser containing an organic substance source and micro- and macronutrients. The organic substance and micro- and macronutrients in the fertiliser are brewing wastes - residual brewing yeast and kieselguhr filter cake, extraction wastes - natural zeolites, chemical industry wastes - phosphogypsum hemihydrate, cement production wastes - cement dust and chalk in ratio (5-31):(1-5):1:(1-2.5):(1-2.5), respectively. ^ EFFECT: invention enables to obtain fertiliser with prolonged effect, which is environmentally safe and can restore and improve soil structure. ^ 1 tbl, 2 ex

column12: METHOD FOR DEVELOPMENT OF MULTILAYER INHOMOGENEOUS OIL DEPOSIT
column13: FIELD: oil and gas industry.SUBSTANCE: invention relates to oil industry, in particular, to methods for development of hard-to-recover oil reserves of dense heterogeneous permeability reservoirs. To implement method for development of multilayer heterogeneous oil deposit, drilling of vertical injection wells and production wells is carried out in underlying low-permeable bed and in overlying impermeable kerogen-containing formation. Wellbores are perforated with subsequent hydraulic fracturing of each formation by fluid on hydrocarbon basis with preservation of hydrodynamic isolation of formations. Proppant cracks are pumped into the formed system and an oxygen-containing agent is pumped into the injection well of the impermeable kerogen-containing formation to create an oxidation zone with high temperature. Production well of the obtained product of in-situ transformation of the oxygen-containing agent is performed along the production well, it is subjected to separation from liquid fractions of hydrocarbons and the produced inert gas agent is pumped to the injection well of the low-permeable oil-bearing bed. Oil is lifted through production well from low-permeable bed. Injection and production wells are drilled in impenetrable kerogen-containing formation at distance from each other, not less than radius of zone of complete oxygen consumption at injection of oxygen-containing agent.EFFECT: providing higher degree of mixability in low-permeable oil formations and displacing inert gas agent consisting of products of in-situ burning of kerogen-containing formations, which causes high degree of oil displacement from low-permeable reservoirs when performing joint development of different permeability beds.1 cl, 2 dwg
